"{\"uid\": \"myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com-news-nepal-olympic-committee-bids-farewell-to-nepali-ski-team-1\", \"text\": \"Subscribe Now  KATHMANDU, Feb\\u00a028: Nepal Olympic Committee officials bade farewell to a six-member ski team to China on Tuesday.  The Nepali team will participate in the the FIS Development Programme - Alpine Training Camp 2024 at Baidahu Ski Resort in Jilin Province, China, from February 29 to March 8. The team includes four players Dinesh Kumar Bohara, Debora Timalsina, Laxmi Rai, and Ujjwal Giri.  Sworaj Shrestha is the team manager and Saphal Shrestha is the coach Following the training camp, the team members will also participate in the 32nd Alpine Ski Championship (Junior) to be held at Baidahu Ski Resort from March 9 to March 10.  NOC General Secretary Nilendra Raj Shrestha and Treasurer Ratan Kumar Tandon bade the players farewell and extended their best wishes to the team. NOC has expressed its full support and encouragement to the team. Representatives of Nepal Ski Association were also present during the program.  Ballot Box Revolt: What RSP's breakthrough victory...  Warning, Threat or Opportunity? Nepal's major part...  Granary in crisis: Water politics leave Madhesh pa...  \\\"China stands ready to work with Nepal to carry forward the traditional friendship, deepen practical cooperation and advance bilateral relations\\\", read the statement.  Building Nepal's Digital Future  Fuel shortages in Nepal: A hidden threat to health a...  Second Innings of Balen and Gagan  Who will become Balen's climate pilot?  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth toward drug addiction.<...  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth toward drug addiction.<...  ANFA CEO Indraman Tuladhar said the ANFA submitted all necessary documents regarding foreign players' visas to the Ministry o